			<h2>Documentation &amp; Tools</h2>

			

			<div class="k-article">

				<div class="k-intro">

				    <p>Kawwa is not just about "building html pages", it is also a way to transfer
				     the knowledge and the experience that we at the Studio have been collecting about usability, 
				     accessibility, (X)HTML coding and css design.</p>

				</div>

			    <p>Hereafter you will find the current available documentation we've been producing to help you create better web products.</p>

			    <p>You will also find valuable information about the Kawwa Portal and Kawwa Compliance in the following pages:</p>

			    <ul class="k-links-list">

			    	<li><a t:type="pageLink" t:page="AboutKawwa">All About Kawwa</a></li>

			    	<li><a t:type="pageLink" t:page="FAQ">FAQ</a></li>

			    </ul>

			    <div class="k-notes">

			    	<p>Notice that, today, not all documents are available in both languages, but all translations will be added in time.</p>

			    </div>

			

